\section{Introduction}
A pascal unit with the name `Process' must be made, containing the procedures and functions defined in the following section.

The specification language used is `Hoare logic'.

In this specification we use a (global) variable A, wich is a list of integers, initially empty.

\section{Functions}
\subsection{Add(n)}
Pascal function declaration: \\
\texttt{procedure Add (var n : integer);}

Specification: \\
\begin{math}
\{ A = A' \land n \in \mathbb{Z} \} \\
Add(n) \\
\{ (((\exists x : x \in \mathbb{Z} : n = x^3) \land (\neg n \inlist A)) \implies (A = A' \concat [n])) \land \\
((\neg(\exists x : x \in \mathbb{Z} : n = x^3) \lor (n \inlist A)) \implies (A = A')) \}
\end{math}

\subsection{Sort()}
Pascal function declaration: \\
\texttt{procedure Sort ();}

Specification: \\
\begin{math}
\{ A = A' \} \\
Sort() \\
\{ ( \forall i \in \mathbb{N} : 0 \leq i < \#A - 1 : A[i] \leq A[i+1] ) \land \\
(\forall n \in \mathbb{N} : \#\{i | 0 \leq i < \#A \land A[i] = n\} = \#\{i | 0 \leq i < \#A' \land A'[i] = n\}) \}
\end{math}

\subsection{Median()}
Pascal function declaration: \\
\texttt{function Median () : integer;}

Specification: \\
\begin{math}
\{ ( \forall i \in \mathbb{N} : 0 \leq i < \#A - 1 : A[i] \leq A[i+1] ) \} \\
Median() \\
\{ (\#A > 0 \implies result = A[\: \lfloor \frac{\#A}{2} \rfloor \:]) \land (\#A = 0 \implies result = nil) \}
\end{math}

Returns: \\
The value of `result' must be returned by the Median function.

